properties.name: Mom's House
properties.description: Located about a mile off of Main Street in Manasqun my mom's house is one of the two locations I called home from 2008 until a few months ago. The bike path, which was located in our back yard, offered wonderful space for exercize and an easy access to the park, town, and Allaire State Park. Her house is ranch style with a stone front and cedar siding around the back. It is three bedrooms and has a relatively large back yard with a deck for entertaining.

properties.name: Dad's House
properties.description: My dad's house is located in Sea Girt, NJ a few blocks from the beach. His road features a dead end at the southern-most point, and ends with a cemetary in the north. His house is backwards Victorian style with three bedrooms and two stories with a finished basement. This is where I grew up as well as spent half of my time from 2008 until last month.

properties.name: Home
properties.description: This is my new house in Deal, NJ. I moved in here a month ago with two of my friends. We have three bedrooms and are approximately two miles off campus. While the neighborhood is very nice we have a fire station to our right and a train to our left, so it can often be a bit loud. We will have this rental for approximately eight more months.

properties.name: Matthew's House
properties.description: Matthew, my boyfriend, recently moved into this new condo complex close to his work in Edison, NJ. He is located on the second floor in a two bedroom, one bath unit. The surrounding area is quiet, with a primarily Asian population. The Municipal complex and town park is in his backyard.

properties.name: Harpoon Willy's
properties.description: Harpoon Willy's is where I work as a hostess a few nights a week. Located on the Manasquan River it is one of the most popular resturaunts in the area for locals and offers a beautiful view. It is situated on a quiet road behind a marina, which blocks most of the traffic noise.

properties.name: Kaitie and Chris' House
properties.description: Kaitie and Chris are the parents of Vivian and Quinn who are both my students. I go to thier house once to twice a week to teach them latin and art. It is three bedrooms and is in a quiet neighborhood a few blocks from a park.

properties.name: School
properties.description: Monmouth University is currently where I am working to complete my BA in Anthropology with minors in Archaeology and History. While there are approximately seven different buildings that one can have classes in, my classes are restricted to only Bey Hall and Howard Hall. Th campus itself is beautifully manicured and has not only the historically significant Wilson Hall, but also the historic library. The south side of campus contains the academic buildings, while the north includes the dorms and the library.
